npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
-d =--save-dev flag
postcss =PostCSS is used to process your CSS file and remove any unused styles ,making the final build smaller and more efficient.
autoprefixer = Autoprefixer is a PostCSS plugin that automatically adds browser vendor prefixes to your CSS rules to ensure compatibility across all browsers.
For example, modern CSS might use properties like display: grid;, but older browsers require a prefix like -ms-grid to support it.
Autoprefixer analyzes your CSS and automatically adds the necessary prefixes for the target browsers you want to support (defined in a .browserslistrc file or in the Tailwind config).